From 294ec73a77d402489e4dabba356c58fbd498f6bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 04:10:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add two evidence-based laser hair removal blog posts,
 cross-link care pages, fix unsourced claims

New posts (PubMed-sourced, both attributed with DOI citations):
- blog/laser-hair-removal-ingrown-hairs-prevention.html: what causes post-laser
  ingrown hairs/bumps and evidence-based prevention (Schuler et al. 2020;
  Jasterzbski & Schwartz 2015; Dalia et al. 2023; Ribera et al. 2010).
- blog/laser-hair-removal-during-period-pain-evidence.html: whether menstrual
  cycle affects laser pain/safety, grounded in pain-research literature
  (Bartley & Rhudy 2013; Fillingim et al. 1997; Kuczmierczyk & Adams 1986;
  Guardiano & Norwood 2005).

Both added to sitemap.xml (self-canonical) and blog/index.html.

Cross-linking (fixes orphaned /laser-hair-removal-protocol.html and closes the
content gaps identified in the pre/post laser hair removal review):
- care/laser-hair-removal-care.html and pre-post-laser-hair-removal.html: added
  a pregnancy/medication/keloid contraindications callout, an ingrown-hairs
  aftercare note, two new FAQ entries (period + ingrown hairs), and a Related
  Reading block linking to the protocol page, both new posts, and the existing
  pregnancy-safety post.
- laser-hair-removal-protocol.html: added ingrown-hairs aftercare note and a
  Related Reading block back to the care guide and both new posts.

Evidence audit of existing articles (per request to ensure claims are backed by
research, not opinion):
- how-to-prepare-for-first-laser-hair-removal-session.html: replaced the
  unsourced "no safety issue" period FAQ with a properly hedged, sourced answer
  linking to the new evidence review.
- understanding-melasma.html: corrected an unsourced "50-70% of pregnancies"
  statistic and an absolute "retinoids not safe" claim to match the real,
  cited figures and nuance already established in melasma-in-pregnancy-chloasma.html
  (Ortonne et al. 2009; Chien et al. 2016).
- laser-hair-removal-for-pcos.html: corrected an outdated "6-month isotretinoin
  gap" claim -- consensus reviews found insufficient evidence to justify
  delaying laser hair removal specifically (Spring et al. 2017 JAMA Dermatol;
  Waldman et al. 2017 ASDS Task Force).
- laser-hair-removal-vs-waxing.html: replaced a vague "80-90%, clinical
  studies show" claim with the real sourced figure (68-82%, Ross/Ibrahimi/
  Kilmer 2018) already used in laser-hair-removal-how-many-sessions-science.html,
  and removed a "waxing makes hair coarser" myth claim.
- post-pregnancy-body-plan.html: softened unsupported breastfeeding-safety
  assertions (fat freeze/Jordi Shape/HIFEM) to reflect that lactation-specific
  safety data is limited and this is a case-by-case dermatologist decision.

A broader pass found ~19 older blog posts with no citations/sources section at
all -- flagged separately as a larger follow-up rather than rewritten wholesale
in this commit.
