+          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
+          <div class="faq">
+            <div class="faq__item">
+              <button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Is it safe to get laser hair removal during your period?</button>
+              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Yes. Menstruation is not on any recognised contraindication list for laser hair removal — the established contraindications are pregnancy/breastfeeding, active skin infection, recent tan or sunburn, certain photosensitising medications, and a history of keloid scarring.</p></div>
+            </div>
+            <div class="faq__item">
+              <button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Does your period make laser hair removal hurt more?</button>
+              <div class="faq__answer"><p>The best-designed pain research finds little to no difference in most pain measures between menstrual cycle phases, and thermal pain specifically — the type most relevant to a laser's heat sensation — did not vary significantly across the cycle in a controlled study. Some women still report feeling more generally tender premenstrually, which is a valid personal reason to reschedule even without a strong physiological signal in the research.</p></div>
+            </div>
+            <div class="faq__item">
+              <button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Do women feel more or less pain than men during laser hair removal?</button>
+              <div class="faq__answer"><p>In a direct clinical study of Nd:YAG laser hair removal, female patients reported lower pain scores than male patients undergoing the same treatment.</p></div>
+            </div>
+          </div>
+        </section>
