+            "text": "Yes, but let your dermatologist know all medications. Isotretinoin (sometimes prescribed for PCOS-related acne) was traditionally thought to require a 6-month gap before laser, but consensus reviews of the evidence found insufficient data to justify delaying laser hair removal specifically for patients on or recently after isotretinoin (Spring et al., 2017; Waldman et al., 2017). Your dermatologist will still make the final call based on your individual case."
