 <p>Your dermatologist will look at: skin laxity (loose skin), fat distribution (where it's stubborn), diastasis recti (abdominal separation), stretch marks (fresh red vs old white), and cellulite. Every plan is personalised based on this.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 2: Address Fat and Skin</h2>
-<p><a href="/services/fat-freeze">Fat Freeze</a> for persistent belly and love-handle pockets. <a href="/services/jordi-shape">Jordi Shape</a> for cellulite, skin firming, and lymphatic drainage. These are safe non-invasive options that don't interfere with breastfeeding (with dermatologist clearance).</p>
+<p><a href="/services/fat-freeze">Fat Freeze</a> for persistent belly and love-handle pockets. <a href="/services/jordi-shape">Jordi Shape</a> for cellulite, skin firming, and lymphatic drainage. Discuss timing with your dermatologist if you're breastfeeding — safety data specific to lactation is limited, so this is decided case-by-case rather than assumed.</p>
 
 <h2>Stage 3: Rebuild Core Strength</h2>
 <p><a href="/services/hifem-body-toning">HIFEM Body Toning</a> is a game-changer for post-pregnancy core weakness and diastasis recti. It stimulates muscle contractions equivalent to thousands of crunches. 4 sessions per area over 2 weeks.</p>
