           "name": "Does pregnancy always trigger melasma?",
           "acceptedAnswer": {
             "@type": "Answer",
-            "text": "About 50–70% of pregnancies trigger melasma. It can fade postpartum but often needs treatment for full clearance."
+            "text": "Pregnancy is one of the most consistent triggers for melasma: a global survey of 324 women with melasma found 26% reported onset during pregnancy and 42% reported onset in the months after delivery (Ortonne et al., 2009). It can fade postpartum but often needs treatment for full clearance."
