           <div class="faq__item"><button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">When can I resume my normal skincare routine?</button><div class="faq__answer"><p>Gentle cleansers and fragrance-free moisturisers are fine from day one. Reintroduce actives (retinoids, AHAs, BHAs, vitamin C) on the treated area after 5–7 days once any redness has fully settled.</p></div></div>
           <div class="faq__item"><button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Can I apply deodorant after underarm laser?</button><div class="faq__answer"><p>Wait 24 hours before applying regular deodorant to freshly treated underarms. If irritation continues, switch to a fragrance-free version for a few days.</p></div></div>
           <div class="faq__item"><button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">What if I forgot to shave before my session?</button><div class="faq__answer"><p>Please call us before you leave home — we can either reschedule or shave the area at the clinic if time permits. Never attempt to trim with scissors right before treatment.</p></div></div>
+          <div class="faq__item"><button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Can I get laser hair removal during my period?</button><div class="faq__answer"><p>Yes — there is no safety contraindication. Some pain-research literature suggests pain perception can vary slightly across the menstrual cycle, but the evidence isn't consistent enough to recommend avoiding any particular phase. See our <a href="/blog/laser-hair-removal-during-period-pain-evidence">evidence review</a> for details.</p></div></div>
+          <div class="faq__item"><button class="faq__question" aria-expanded="false">Is it normal to get small bumps or ingrown hairs after laser?</button><div class="faq__answer"><p>Occasional bumps or ingrown hairs can occur as treated hair sheds, and they're usually temporary. Gentle exfoliation once any redness has settled, and avoiding tight clothing over the area in the days after treatment, both help reduce the risk. See our <a href="/blog/laser-hair-removal-ingrown-hairs-prevention">full guide</a> for the evidence behind these recommendations.</p></div></div>
         </div>
       </div>
     </section>
 
